      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(sessions-files): exclude workspace-external files from workspace rail list",
        "body": "Fixes #95685\n\n## What Problem This Solves\n\nThe Session Workspace Rail (right sidebar, added in 2026.6.9) marks files outside the configured workspace directory as \"missing\" (red badge), even though those files exist and were successfully read during the session. This is confusing because users see alarming red markers for files that are perfectly fine.\n\n## Evidence\n\n### Fix\n\nIn `buildListResult()`, filter out files that are outside the configured workspace directory before returning the file list. The check uses the existing `resolveTouchedFilePath()` to determine whether a file path resolves inside the workspace root.\n\n- Files inside the workspace that genuinely don't exist on disk still show as `missing: true` ✓\n- Files outside the workspace (e.g. `/usr/lib/node_modules/...`) are excluded from the list ✓\n- The browser explorer view is unaffected — it only shows workspace-internal files anyway\n\n### Tests\n\nAll 30 existing tests pass (no behavior change for workspace-internal files):\n\n```\nTest Files  2 passed (2)\nTests  30 passed (30)\n```\n\n### Checks\n- Format: `oxfmt` ✓\n- Lint: `oxlint` ✓\n- Diff: +19 source, -3 source (22 lines)\n- Branch: clean from `origin/main`",
